    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix buffer overflow in UECapabilityEnquiry message generation\n\n### Summary\nThe `rrc_gNB_generate_UECapabilityEnquiry` function in the gNB RRC module was using a hardcoded 100-byte buffer for ASN.1 encoding, which could lead to buffer overflows when generating UECapabilityEnquiry messages with certain band configurations. This caused crashes during the RRC setup procedure, particularly when the encoded message exceeded 100 bytes.\n\nThe issue was identified when testing with specific UE capabilities that resulted in larger encoded messages. The function would either crash during encoding or send malformed RRC messages to the UE, causing connection failures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/rrc_gNB.c`: Increased buffer size from 100 bytes to `NR_RRC_BUF_SIZE` (4096 bytes) and added bounds checking\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/MESSAGES/asn1_msg.c`: Modified `do_NR_SA_UECapabilityEnquiry` to accept buffer size parameter and use it in encoding\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/MESSAGES/asn1_msg.h`: Updated function signature to include buffer size parameter\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/MESSAGES/tests/test_asn1_msg.cpp`: Updated test case to pass buffer size parameter\n\n"
}